#Dave's Code for responce ratio
logRR <- function(ford){
  ford$treatment <- ford$treatment[drop=T]
  trt <- levels(ford$treatment)
  trt.no <- length(trt)-1
  means <- with(ford,tapply(AFDM,treatment,mean,na.rm=T))
  sds <- with(ford,tapply(AFDM,treatment,sd,na.rm=T))
  ns <- with(ford,tapply(AFDM,treatment,length))
  logRR <- vector(length=trt.no)
  seRR <- vector(length=trt.no)
  
  for(i in 1:trt.no){
    logRR[i] <- round(log(means[i+1])-log(means[1]),3)
    sp2 <- (((ns[1]-1)*sds[1]^2+(ns[i+1]-1)*sds[i+1]^2)/(ns[1]+ns[i+1]-2))
    seRR[i] <- round(sqrt(sp2*(1/(means[1]^2*ns[1])+1/(means[i+1]^2*ns[i+1]))),3)
    
  }
  res <- data.frame(trt[-1],logRR,seRR,row.names=NULL)
  colnames(res)<-c("Treatment","logRR","seRR")
  return(res)
}
FordRR<-logRR(ford)
### how do I plot this???
par(mfrow=c(1,1))
plot(logRR~Treatment, data=FordRR, las=2)

#Dave's Code for responce ratio
logRRGB <- function(greenbay){
  greenbay$treatment <- greenbay$treatment[drop=T]
  trt <- levels(greenbay$treatment)
  trt.no <- length(trt)-1
  means <- with(greenbay,tapply(AFDM,treatment,mean,na.rm=T))
  sds <- with(greenbay,tapply(AFDM,treatment,sd,na.rm=T))
  ns <- with(greenbay,tapply(AFDM,treatment,length))
  logRRGB <- vector(length=trt.no)
  seRR <- vector(length=trt.no)
  
  for(i in 1:trt.no){
    logRRGB[i] <- round(log(means[i+1])-log(means[1]),3)
    sp2 <- (((ns[1]-1)*sds[1]^2+(ns[i+1]-1)*sds[i+1]^2)/(ns[1]+ns[i+1]-2))
    seRR[i] <- round(sqrt(sp2*(1/(means[1]^2*ns[1])+1/(means[i+1]^2*ns[i+1]))),3)
    
  }
  res <- data.frame(trt[-1],logRRGB,seRR,row.names=NULL)
  colnames(res)<-c("Treatment","logRRGB","seRR")
  return(res)
}
GreenBayRR<-logRRGB(greenbay)
### how do I plot this???
par(mfrow=c(1,1))
plot(logRRGB~Treatment, data=GreenBayRR, las=2)

#Dave's Code for responce ratio
logRRNE <- function(nerie){
  nerie$treatment <- nerie$treatment[drop=T]
  trt <- levels(nerie$treatment)
  trt.no <- length(trt)-1
  means <- with(nerie,tapply(AFDM,treatment,mean,na.rm=T))
  sds <- with(nerie,tapply(AFDM,treatment,sd,na.rm=T))
  ns <- with(nerie,tapply(AFDM,treatment,length))
  logRRNE <- vector(length=trt.no)
  seRR <- vector(length=trt.no)
  
  for(i in 1:trt.no){
    logRRNE[i] <- round(log(means[i+1])-log(means[1]),3)
    sp2 <- (((ns[1]-1)*sds[1]^2+(ns[i+1]-1)*sds[i+1]^2)/(ns[1]+ns[i+1]-2))
    seRR[i] <- round(sqrt(sp2*(1/(means[1]^2*ns[1])+1/(means[i+1]^2*ns[i+1]))),3)
    
  }
  res <- data.frame(trt[-1],logRRNE,seRR,row.names=NULL)
  colnames(res)<-c("Treatment","logRRNE","seRR")
  return(res)
}

#Dave's Code for responce ratio
logRRM <- function(maumee){
  maumee$treatment <- maumee$treatment[drop=T]
  trt <- levels(maumee$treatment)
  trt.no <- length(trt)-1
  means <- with(maumee,tapply(AFDM,treatment,mean,na.rm=T))
  sds <- with(maumee,tapply(AFDM,treatment,sd,na.rm=T))
  ns <- with(maumee,tapply(AFDM,treatment,length))
  logRRM <- vector(length=trt.no)
  seRR <- vector(length=trt.no)
  
  for(i in 1:trt.no){
    logRRM[i] <- round(log(means[i+1])-log(means[1]),3)
    sp2 <- (((ns[1]-1)*sds[1]^2+(ns[i+1]-1)*sds[i+1]^2)/(ns[1]+ns[i+1]-2))
    seRR[i] <- round(sqrt(sp2*(1/(means[1]^2*ns[1])+1/(means[i+1]^2*ns[i+1]))),3)
    
  }
  res <- data.frame(trt[-1],logRRM,seRR,row.names=NULL)
  colnames(res)<-c("Treatment","logRRM","seRR")
  return(res)
}
MaumeeRR<-logRRM(maumee)
### how do I plot this???
par(mfrow=c(1,1))
plot(logRRM~Treatment, data=MaumeeRR, las=2)

#CHLA linear model, one way ANOVA and Tukey post hoc
maumeeLMchla<-lm(ChlA~treatment, data=maumee)
shapiro.test(resid(maumeeLMchla))

##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  resid(maumeeLMchla)
## W = 0.97979, p-value = 0.7935
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
